ors.%20Whispering%20Wings%20even%20records%20its%20own%20pilot%20announcements%2C%20and%20pairs%20them%20with%20real-life%20communications%20from%20air%20traffic%20control.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20help%20travelers%20focus%20on%20the%20sounds%20of%20flying%20that%20might%20be%20considered%20more%20calming%2C%20without%20all%20the%20crying%20babies%20and%20irate%20passengers.%20%26quot%3BI've%20never%20felt%20this%20at%20peace%20on%20a%20plane%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20commenter%20wrote%20about%20one%20Whispering%20Wings%20video%2C%20which%20follows%20an%20eight-hour%20trip%20from%20Toronto%20to%20Frankfurt%2C%20Germany.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20for%20all%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fasmr-best-sleep-funniest-weirdest-videos-most-tingles-2019-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EASMR's%20popularity%3C%2Fa%3E%20among%20frequent%20flyers%2C%20the%20weirdness%20factor%20has%20kept%20it%20from%20going%20fully%20mainstream.%20%26quot%3BI%20find%20it's%20still%20kept%20quite%20hush-hush%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sasha%20Mukerjea%2C%20an%20events%20marketer%20and%20frequent%20traveler%20who%20uses%20ASMR%20to%20relax%20her%20nerves.%20%26quot%3BSome%20people%20find%20the%20phenomena%20baffling.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20experiencing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideos-designed-to-trigger-asmr-are-surging-in-popularity-2017-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EASMR%20%26quot%3Btingles%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20I%20was%20a%20kid.%20My%20family%20moved%20frequently%20before%20finally%20settling%20in%20Singapore%2C%20and%20I%20used%20to%20seek%20out%20sources%20of%20white%20noise%20as%20a%20way%20to%20relax.%20Once%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fasmr-tiktok-instead-of-youtube-growth-subscribers-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EASMR%20videos%3C%2Fa%3E%20became%20available%2C%20I%20started%20consuming%20them%20like%20aspirin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20specific%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fface-touching-asmr-videos-comfort-touch-deprived-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EASMR%20%26quot%3Btriggers%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20we%20respond%20to%20are%20as%20personal%20as%20our%20taste%20in%20food.%20Tuning%20into%20a%20certain%20sound%20%E2%80%94%20someone%20chomping%20into%20a%20pickle%2C%20say%20%E2%80%94%20may%20gross%20one%20person%20out%20while%20causing%20waves%20of%20pleasant%20chills%20in%20others.%20But%20while%20the%20term%20ASMR%20is%20relatively%20new%2C%20researchers%20say%20the%20response%20itself%20is%20as%20old%20as%20time.%20When%20we%20respond%20to%20soothing%20sounds%2C%20our%20brains%20are%20flooded%20with%20dopamine%20and%20oxytocin%2C%20the%20so-called%20love%20hormone%2C%20creating%20a%20feeling%20of%20euphoria%20that's%20been%20referred%20to%20as%20%26quot%3Bbraingasms.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BASMR%20can%20be%20very%20helpful%20to%20decrease%20the%20stress%20of%20traveling%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Craig%20Richard%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20biopharmaceutical%20sciences%20at%20Shenandoah%20University%20who%20partnered%20with%20JetBlue%20on%20the%20airline's%20ASMR%20content.%20Still%2C%20he%20says%2C%20more%20study%20is%20needed%20to%20better%20understand%20what%20content%20works%20best%20on%20flights%2C%20since%20the%20increased%20pressure%20from%20high%20altitudes%20on%20the%20inner%20ear%20can%20dampen%20the%20body's%20receptiveness%20to%20ASMR.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EASMR%20videos%20aren't%20the%20only%20way%20to%20use%20the%20sounds%20of%20air%20travel%20to%20make%20the%20experience%20of%20air%20travel%20less%20stressful.%20I've%20found%20that%20tuning%20into%20even%20the%20most%20fleeting%20triggers%2C%20like%20the%20ding%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bfasten%20seatbelts%26quot%3B%20sign%2C%20can%20help%20induce%20a%20state%20of%20relaxation%2C%20helping%20to%20lower%20my%20heart%20rate%20and%20provide%20me%20with%20a%20sense%20of%20calm.%20As%20Richard%20explains%20it%2C%20these%20short%20sounds%2C%20if%20tied%20to%20warm%20memories%2C%20may%20trigger%20a%20kind%20of%20Pavlovian%20response%20that%20can%20stimulate%20ASMR%20by%20%26quot%3Breminding%20someone%20of%20pleasant%20travel%20experiences.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20trying%20this%20DIY%20version%20of%20ASMR%20during%20a%20flight%20to%20London.%20It%20was%20my%20first%20trip%20to%20Europe%20since%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20the%20indignity%20of%20modern%20travel%20seemed%20like%20a%20small%20price%20to%20pay%20for%20a%20vacation%20I'd%20been%20craving.%20For%20the%20first%20few%20hours%20of%20the%20flight%2C%20everything%20was%20hunky-dory.%20Then%2C%20three%20rows%20ahead%20of%20me%2C%20a%20baby%20started%20wailing.%20My%20iPhone%20was%20out%20of%20juice%2C%20so%20I%20couldn't%20reach%20for%20my%20tried-and-true%20ASMR%20video.%20I%20tried%20to%20drown%20out%20the%20noise%20by%20cranking%20up%20the%20volume%20on%20%26quot%3BCasino%20Royale%2C%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20in-flight%20movie%20I%20was%20watching.%20But%20not%20even%20007%2C%20with%20his%20license%20to%20kill%2C%20could%20silence%20the%20ceaseless%20cries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20I%20noticed%20that%20the%20two%20passengers%20to%20my%20right%20were%20speaking%20slowly%20and%20softly%20in%20a%20language%20I%20couldn't%20make%20out.%20By%20focusing%20on%20their%20voices%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20restore%20my%20calm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMukerjea%2C%20the%20events%20marketer%20who%20relies%20on%20ASMR%20to%20travel%2C%20recalls%20a%20similar%20experience.%20When%20bad%20weather%20extended%20her%20layover%20in%20Delhi%2C%20at%20one%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F10-busiest-airports-worldwide-2022-atlanta-dallas-denver-travel-rebound-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworld's%20busiest%20airports%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20found%20herself%20overwhelmed%20by%20%26quot%3Bthe%20blistering%20fluorescence%20and%20relentless%20tide%20of